Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-red; cream slip. Circular stamp with rose symbol.
Curator's comments: The piece may have been drawn by Petrie (Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 184, 3, although he gives the full reading. Name Aristokles. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0808)
